There are a number of{Public Footpaths and{Bridleways}in the area. Originally many of these connected outlying hamlets with village centres, or were direct routes from cottages to the farms or, like{Trent Path,}from the village into the town. Nowadays these are used mainly for{recreational {purposes}and although some become very overgrown during late summer, there are enough in good condition to make some lovely{walks.}
